<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
National Grasslands fee adjustments for conservation practices.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 01 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Grazing fees for National Grasslands may be credited up to 50 percent for conservation practices and administrative
costs as provided in paragraphs (a) and (b) of this section.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Credit for Conservation Practices.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 In order to receive credit, requirements for permittee construction or development of conservation practices must
be incorporated into term grazing permits, including grazing agreements, with a provision that credits for such
improvements shall be applied toward the annual grazing fee. Fee credits are allowed only for the following conservation
practices:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Where the Forest Service requires the permittee to construct or develop the conservation practices to meet management
direction contained in relevant forest land and resource management plans, related projects decisions, and the
term grazing permit or grazing agreement.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Where the conservation practices are necessary to achieve or maintain desired vegetation conditions for resource
protection, soil productivity, riparian, watershed and wetland values, wildlife and fisheries habitat, and other
related values.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

